# ~/.claude — public config repo (a.k.a. "dotclaude")
#
# Strategy: IGNORE EVERYTHING by default, then allow-list only the
# portable, secret-free config. ~/.claude's working tree also holds
# credentials and session state, so a deny-all default is what makes a
# PUBLIC repo here safe: `git add -A` can never stage anything that
# isn't explicitly un-ignored below.

# 1) Ignore every top-level entry…
/*

# 2) …then allow only these portable, secret-free paths:
!/.gitignore
!/README.md
!/skills/
!/agents/
!/commands/
!/hooks/

# Reminder: skills/agents/commands/hooks are allow-listed WHOLESALE —
# never drop a secret inside them or it WILL be tracked.

# NEVER allow-list these (here as a reminder, already ignored by /*):
#   .credentials.json   history.jsonl   sessions/   projects/   todos/
#   telemetry/  statsig/  cache/  shell-snapshots/
#   settings.json   CLAUDE.md   (deliberately machine-/personal-specific)
